  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Cleon, 6, poet, from Curium (Cyprus), Author of Argonautiká 
    (but cf. [4])  in several bks., probably in verses, which are quoted in three scholia to the first bk. of
    Apollonius [2] Rhodius. Possibly identical to the Elegist, whose two verses are quoted by the
    EM 389,25-28..." Fornaro, Sotera (Sassari). "Cleon." Brill's New Pauly.
    Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and Helmuth Schneider . 
    Brill, 2009. Brill Online. Tufts University Library.</mads:note>  
